  "texts": [
    "If the NeRF model is adjusted to the one-to-one scale of the real facility, alignment using the entire NeRF model will result in a rendering volume too large to be efficiently manipulated in VR.",
    "Therefore, it is recommended to perform the alignment process by focusing on a small part of the scene for accurate object manipulation.",
    "In the merge step, the user could perceptually validate the alignment by reducing the FoV of the NeRF camera and adjusting the transparency of the shader that renders the NeRF images so that both the CAD drawing and the NeRF rendering are simultaneously visible.",
    "The user can iteratively move back and forth between the alignment and fusion steps until the two 3D representations are spatially aligned.",
    "The relative transformation matrix between the NeRF model and the CAD model can be saved for reuse."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}